01:01:17.140 --> 01:01:21.579
- a multitude of the heavenly host
praising God"...


375
01:01:46.900 --> 01:01:49.059
I love you.

376
01:01:50.660 --> 01:01:55.739
- I love you, Astrid.
- When will the court case be over?


377
01:01:57.500 --> 01:02:00.899
- Soon.
- Oh God...


378
01:02:01.100 --> 01:02:04.819
That little darling.
That little darling!


379
01:02:05.820 --> 01:02:09.939
- I have a Christmas present for you.
- What have I done?


380
01:02:17.300 --> 01:02:19.899
You need to keep warm.

381
01:02:25.140 --> 01:02:27.819
It's beautiful.

382
01:02:29.740 --> 01:02:32.299
You haven't lost him.

383
01:02:34.100 --> 01:02:39.299
He's just in Denmark.
We'll visit him just as soon as we can.


384
01:02:41.100 --> 01:02:43.379
- Our son.
- Our son.


385
01:02:44.740 --> 01:02:46.939
Darling.

386
01:03:15.980 --> 01:03:18.059
You don't have to marry him.

387
01:03:20.980 --> 01:03:24.619
You don't have to.
You'll be a secretary soon.


388
01:03:27.180 --> 01:03:32.299
You really want to be stepmother to
Berta and all her brothers and sisters?


389
01:03:34.820 --> 01:03:37.259
Do you love him?

390
01:03:43.100 --> 01:03:45.339
You don't have to, Astrid.

391
01:03:45.580 --> 01:03:50.059
You could leave the child in Denmark,
come home and forget all of this.


392
01:03:56.060 --> 01:03:58.219
You want me to abandon my baby?

393
01:04:03.460 --> 01:04:06.859
Isn't his foster mother
a good mother to him?


394
01:04:12.100 --> 01:04:14.139
Do you love him?

395
01:04:46.700 --> 01:04:49.179
He's over there.

396
01:04:50.700 --> 01:04:52.979
Here he is...

397
01:05:10.780 --> 01:05:13.539
He's got so big!

398
01:05:13.740 --> 01:05:17.579
- Why don't you pick him up?
- He's really grown!


399
01:05:21.140 --> 01:05:23.899
Hello!

400
01:05:25.980 --> 01:05:29.659
Hello, Lasse!

401
01:05:38.220 --> 01:05:40.179
Let me see him. Come here!

402
01:05:49.780 --> 01:05:52.099
What a handsome boy!

403
01:05:53.220 --> 01:05:55.499
Look!

404
01:06:01.980 --> 01:06:05.899
I'm glad you came.
Not many do.


405
01:06:10.220 --> 01:06:13.619
We'll come and get him
as soon as all this is over.


406
01:06:38.300 --> 01:06:42.139
Swedish Book Depository Radio Division.
This is Astrid Ericsson.


407
01:06:42.340 --> 01:06:44.659
I'll put you through.

408
01:06:45.740 --> 01:06:48.619
Mr Nilsson for Mr Karlsson.

409
01:06:59.220 --> 01:07:02.699
- Swedish Book Depository Radio Division.
- It's me.


410
01:07:06.260 --> 01:07:08.859
How can I help you?

411
01:07:12.500 --> 01:07:14.899
Somebody saw us at the hotel.

412
01:07:18.180 --> 01:07:23.219
Olivia's hired a handwriting expert to
examine my letters to the birth clinic-


413
01:07:23.420 --> 01:07:26.299
- to prove that I'm Axel Gustafsson..

414
01:07:26.500 --> 01:07:29.339
She's got the judge
to postpone the hearing.


415
01:07:32.100 --> 01:07:34.099
I see.

416
01:07:37.460 --> 01:07:40.579
You said I could bring him home.

417
01:07:40.700 --> 01:07:45.579
I know. I'll send you money
so you can visit him.


418
01:07:48.060 --> 01:07:52.379
- Lasse is six months old now!
- I know.


419
01:07:55.060 --> 01:07:58.739
Marie has just written
that he can sit up on his own!


420
01:08:01.340 --> 01:08:04.259
I miss you.

421
01:08:05.420 --> 01:08:07.459
Hello?

422
01:08:09.700 --> 01:08:13.819
Thank you for your call, Mr Gustafsson.
I'll see what I can do.


423
01:08:24.100 --> 01:08:26.499
What is it?

424
01:08:37.580 --> 01:08:41.099
Marie? I think he's hungry again.

425
01:08:47.020 --> 01:08:50.699
Are you already hungry again,
little Lasse?


426
01:08:53.060 --> 01:08:55.979
- He just needs a new nappy.
- Again?


427
01:08:56.180 --> 01:08:58.899
Yes, it's an endless source.

428
01:09:03.300 --> 01:09:05.419
Let's see, Lasse...

429
01:09:08.940 --> 01:09:11.579
I think it opens here...

430
01:09:12.900 --> 01:09:15.099
No... no, like this...

431
01:09:20.100 --> 01:09:22.499
That's better, isn't it?

432
01:09:26.060 --> 01:09:30.899
When we get back, we'll put a bit
of talcum powder on his bottom.


433
01:09:34.980 --> 01:09:39.299
Marie, I don't know
what I'd do without you.


434
01:09:42.620 --> 01:09:45.179
The clock is ticking, Astrid.

435
01:10:06.820 --> 01:10:11.339
The children in your books
can overcome almost anything.


436
01:10:11.580 --> 01:10:15.299
Pippi gets along
without her mother and father.


437
01:10:15.460 --> 01:10:19.939
Emil is never scared, even when he gets
punished and locked in the woodshed.


438
01:10:23.420 --> 01:10:26.779
MO is starving
and thinks he's going to die,


439
01:10:26.980 --> 01:10:30.299
but he wins out
over evil in the end..

440
01:10:31.740 --> 01:10:35.059
That's what I want to be,
someone who never gives up-


441
01:10:35.220 --> 01:10:39.579
- but keeps fighting,
even if I'm hungry and feel alone.


442
01:11:09.380 --> 01:11:11.499
- Hello.
- Hello.


443
01:11:18.540 --> 01:11:21.499
I was found guilty of adultery.

444
01:11:29.140 --> 01:11:31.819
I was fined 1,000 kronor.

445
01:11:33.660 --> 01:11:36.259
1,000 kronor?

446
01:11:38.500 --> 01:11:41.419
- You're not going to prison?
- No.


447
01:11:46.180 --> 01:11:49.739
Evidently it's cheap
to be a philanderer.


448
01:11:52.020 --> 01:11:54.979
But you said that you risked
going to prison.


449
01:11:55.140 --> 01:11:59.059
I got away with a fine,
so it all worked out.


450
01:12:03.980 --> 01:12:07.939
- So I can bring Lasse home?
- You can bring Lasse home.


451
01:12:31.420 --> 01:12:34.339
I've booked us a room.

452
01:12:41.820 --> 01:12:46.539
We're free, Astrid. We can do
whatever the hell we want.


453
01:13:09.500 --> 01:13:11.459
Marry me.

454
01:13:27.940 --> 01:13:32.259
We can have a spring wedding.
With blossoming apple trees!


455
01:13:35.100 --> 01:13:38.579
- It's way too big.
- Darling...


456
01:13:40.060 --> 01:13:42.819
I'll get the jeweller to adjust it.

457
01:13:44.220 --> 01:13:48.179
- You have to see the drawings.
- Drawings?


458
01:13:50.380 --> 01:13:54.219
We'll redo the house
so you can have a new kitchen.


459
01:13:54.380 --> 01:13:57.379
Berta will move
up to the attic room.


460
01:13:57.580 --> 01:14:01.179
Then Lasse can have her old room.

461
01:14:01.340 --> 01:14:05.619
So you can comfort him
if he cries in the night.


462
01:14:08.820 --> 01:14:13.179
Darling?
Come here. Come and see.


463
01:14:18.540 --> 01:14:21.979
- You said you could end up in prison.
- Yes.


464
01:14:23.620 --> 01:14:26.659
And all this was just for money?
For 1,000 kronor?


465
01:14:26.820 --> 01:14:30.299
I couldn't have known that.

466
01:14:32.500 --> 01:14:36.259
- Lasse's been hidden away for a year!
- That was your idea.


467
01:14:36.420 --> 01:14:40.939
I didn't ask you to take him to Denmark!
That was your lady lawyer.


468
01:14:44.540 --> 01:14:46.979
Hey... Darling...

469
01:14:47.140 --> 01:14:49.419
Why can't we just be happy?

470
01:14:50.940 --> 01:14:55.779
- Redo the kitchen and start a family?
- I'm sorry, I can't.


471
01:14:55.940 --> 01:14:59.019
- I love you.
- I can't.


472
01:15:00.660 --> 01:15:03.819
I just need some time to think.

473
01:15:14.100 --> 01:15:17.539
- Tell me what I've done wrong!
- You're hurting me!


474
01:15:19.260 --> 01:15:22.259
What do you need to think about?

475
01:15:22.380 --> 01:15:27.059
You can't look after a child.
You can barely afford food.


476
01:15:27.220 --> 01:15:30.259
- You realise the bank is closing now?
- Yes.


477
01:15:31.700 --> 01:15:34.299
- Damn it...
- That hurts!


478
01:15:36.740 --> 01:15:39.099
Tell me what I've done.

479
01:15:40.340 --> 01:15:42.779
Am I too old?

480
01:15:48.460 --> 01:15:51.299
How will you manage without me?

481
01:16:12.980 --> 01:16:16.099
I can't come, Marie.
I don't have any money.


482
01:16:16.260 --> 01:16:20.339
No. I'm sorry to hear about you two..

483
01:16:20.580 --> 01:16:24.139
- How is Lasse?
- He's fine.


484
01:16:24.340 --> 01:16:26.659
He can stay as long as you like..

485
01:16:26.820 --> 01:16:30.939
- Could I hear his voice?
- Lasse, say hello to Lassa-mama.


486
01:16:31.100 --> 01:16:35.819
- Hello, Lasse! Are you doing okay?
- No.


487
01:16:35.980 --> 01:16:39.179
- Tell her what you and Esse did today. '
- No!


488
01:16:40.620 --> 01:16:44.379
- I can't afford to talk anymore, Marie.
- Of course.


489
01:16:45.900 --> 01:16:48.859
Come now, Lasse.
Say bye-bye to Lasse-mama.


490
01:16:50.340 --> 01:16:52.979
- Goodbye.
- Goodbye.


491
01:17:28.620 --> 01:17:32.059
How did the interview
with the Royal Automobile Club go?


492
01:17:32.180 --> 01:17:35.379
I hope it went well.

493
01:17:35.580 --> 01:17:40.579
If I get it I can afford a flat of
my own. Then Lasse can live with me.


494
01:17:42.140 --> 01:17:44.699
What book did you get?

495
01:17:46.260 --> 01:17:48.859
- "Hunger" by Hamsun.
- Let me see.


496
01:17:57.940 --> 01:18:01.499
"I had reached hunger's joyful madness.

497
01:18:01.700 --> 01:18:06.379
"I was empty and without pain,
and my thoughts were untrammelled. "


498
01:18:14.940 --> 01:18:17.419
You couldn't get a simple love story?

499
01:18:31.900 --> 01:18:35.299
- The yearbook. I asked for...
- They're ready now.


500
01:18:35.500 --> 01:18:39.899
One moment. I asked
for these captions to be corrected.


501
01:18:40.100 --> 01:18:43.059
And this hasn't been proof-read.

502
01:18:43.220 --> 01:18:49.139
That's the old manuscript.
This is the proofed and corrected one.


503
01:18:57.700 --> 01:19:00.899
This manuscript
is to be sent to the printer.


504
01:19:02.340 --> 01:19:05.099
Yes, and a messenger is on his way.

505
01:19:06.340 --> 01:19:10.099
- In other words, everything's in order.
- Yes.


506
01:19:12.340 --> 01:19:14.979
Excellent, thank you.

507
01:19:20.140 --> 01:19:24.979
- How old is your son?
- He's two and a half.


508
01:19:26.300 --> 01:19:29.259
I can look after him
while you work.


509
01:19:29.420 --> 01:19:33.299
My daughter has a child's bed
that we don't use anymore.


510
01:19:34.780 --> 01:19:39.899
The toilet is in the courtyard
and there's a bathhouse near the park.


511
01:19:40.060 --> 01:19:43.539
The kitchen is at the end of the hall.
Excuse me...


512
01:19:53.100 --> 01:19:56.219
Don't you think
Lasse will be happy here?


513
01:19:58.620 --> 01:20:01.339
- Just the red ones!
- Okay.


514
01:20:06.740 --> 01:20:09.259
Just pick the very reddest ones.

515
01:20:10.620 --> 01:20:14.819
- Look at mine, Mum!
- Aren't they nice!


516
01:20:17.820 --> 01:20:20.419
He hears Carl calling me Mum.

517
01:20:21.500 --> 01:20:24.379
Esse calls me Mum too.

518
01:20:24.620 --> 01:20:27.299
But we talk a lot about you,
Lasse-mama.


519
01:20:33.980 --> 01:20:37.099
Marie... Should I tell him?

520
01:20:38.380 --> 01:20:43.579
I think it's best if we do it together,
tell him he's going to live with you.


521
01:20:45.340 --> 01:20:50.459
- What will we say?
- That you've found a place to live.


522
01:20:51.700 --> 01:20:54.579
He knows you're his mother.

523
01:21:06.260 --> 01:21:09.059
Look how many you've picked!

524
01:21:10.100 --> 01:21:12.859
Look how many you've picked!

525
01:21:19.500 --> 01:21:21.699
Can you take this?

526
01:21:24.180 --> 01:21:28.339
I'll tuck Esse in
and Lasse-mama will tuck Lasse in.


527
01:21:28.500 --> 01:21:30.619
No!

528
01:21:33.140 --> 01:21:34.099
Come.

529
01:21:34.300 --> 01:21:38.099
- No!
- Come now. She's here today.


530
01:21:39.980 --> 01:21:44.339
- No!
- I can tell really good stories!


531
01:21:44.540 --> 01:21:47.659
Lassen.
Go to Lasse-mama now.


532
01:21:52.620 --> 01:21:55.179
I want you to tuck me in, Mum!

533
01:22:03.300 --> 01:22:06.939
It's been a long day, he's tired.
I'll put him to bed.


534
01:22:07.140 --> 01:22:09.219
Carl, can you take care of Esse'?

535
01:22:09.420 --> 01:22:14.059
- Can you say goodnight, Lasse-mama?
- Goodnight, Lasse-mama.


536
01:22:14.220 --> 01:22:16.499
Goodnight.

537
01:22:21.620 --> 01:22:24.499
I want to sleep in your bed, Mum.

538
01:23:02.940 --> 01:23:06.339
I'm not his mother, Marie.

539
01:23:06.540 --> 01:23:11.059
- You are his mother.
- Marie, he doesn't know me!


540
01:23:11.180 --> 01:23:14.179
He doesn't even know me!

541
01:23:20.140 --> 01:23:23.379
Can't you see that this is his home?

542
01:23:27.140 --> 01:23:29.819
That you're the one he loves?

543
01:23:35.860 --> 01:23:38.819
You gave birth to him.
You're his mother.


544
01:23:39.020 --> 01:23:41.619
I've just looked after him.

545
01:23:43.620 --> 01:23:45.859
This is his home.

546
01:23:46.060 --> 01:23:51.059
Mum?

547
01:23:55.060 --> 01:23:57.299
He's calling you.

548
01:24:00.340 --> 01:24:01.779
Mum!

549
01:24:27.820 --> 01:24:30.419
Can you say goodbye?

550
01:24:33.140 --> 01:24:35.859
I'm going now.

551
01:24:43.060 --> 01:24:46.659
Lasse, can you say goodbye
nicely to Lasse-mama?


552
01:24:51.060 --> 01:24:53.739
Shall we say goodbye, Lasse?

553
01:25:45.260 --> 01:25:49.739
Welcome to the annual party
of the Royal Automobile Club.


554
01:25:49.940 --> 01:25:53.579
I assure you that we'll soon be eating.

555
01:25:55.180 --> 01:25:58.779
But before that,
I think we should raise our glasses-


556
01:25:58.940 --> 01:26:04.179
- and drink a toast to another good,
prosperous year for motoring.


557
01:26:04.340 --> 01:26:06.499
Cheers!

558
01:26:13.740 --> 01:26:16.339
Still toasting motoring?

559
01:26:19.740 --> 01:26:22.419
And thank you for the notes.

560
01:26:22.620 --> 01:26:25.659
They were more entertaining
than the actual meetings.


561
01:26:25.820 --> 01:26:28.579
Long live motoring!

562
01:27:37.100 --> 01:27:39.619
Excuse me a moment.
Oops, sorry.


563
01:27:45.220 --> 01:27:47.299
May I?

564
01:28:18.140 --> 01:28:22.139
- Should I call you a cab?
- No.


565
01:28:22.340 --> 01:28:24.979
- Are you sure?
- Yes.


566
01:30:02.780 --> 01:30:05.099
Get up.

567
01:30:14.940 --> 01:30:16.899
You did the right thing.

568
01:30:48.780 --> 01:30:51.219
You've grown big.

569
01:30:54.780 --> 01:30:57.979
Astrid?

570
01:30:58.100 --> 01:31:00.979
Come here. Come now.

571
01:31:13.460 --> 01:31:15.859
- What is it?
- This came for you.


572
01:31:45.380 --> 01:31:48.339
Marie is ill.

573
01:31:48.580 --> 01:31:51.099
It's serious.

574
01:31:53.100 --> 01:31:56.779
She's asking what I want to do
about Lasse.


575
01:31:56.980 --> 01:31:58.819
Do about him?

576
01:31:59.020 --> 01:32:02.739
It's serious.
She can't look after him anymore.


577
01:32:07.660 --> 01:32:10.539
You must stay strong.

578
01:32:12.260 --> 01:32:14.859
But he's my son!

579
01:32:16.580 --> 01:32:19.219
He has no one else in the world!

580
01:32:25.140 --> 01:32:27.219
Are you not my mother?

581
01:32:29.700 --> 01:32:32.379
Isn't he your grandson?

582
01:32:56.900 --> 01:33:02.259
- She only wants what's best for you.
- Do you think I should abandon him?


583
01:33:02.460 --> 01:33:07.979
Your mother worries about you.
She thinks about you night and day.


584
01:33:08.140 --> 01:33:12.139
Are you my father?
Is he your grandson?


585
01:33:15.460 --> 01:33:17.899
I don't know what to say.

586
01:33:23.100 --> 01:33:25.219
You don't know what to say?

587
01:33:25.380 --> 01:33:29.699
You're my father
and you don't know anything?


588
01:33:31.740 --> 01:33:33.139
Guess what!

589
01:33:33.300 --> 01:33:38.779
I'm not coming back until I'm welcome
with my son! Your grandson!


590
01:33:38.940 --> 01:33:41.499
Do you understand that?

591
01:35:02.100 --> 01:35:03.859
Marie?

592
01:35:07.740 --> 01:35:10.059
Hello.

593
01:35:17.460 --> 01:35:19.739
I can't look after him anymore.

594
01:35:24.740 --> 01:35:28.179
I don't know if I can...
I can't do this without you.


595
01:35:34.060 --> 01:35:36.819
You must be his mother.

596
01:35:39.300 --> 01:35:41.939
You can do this.

597
01:35:43.980 --> 01:35:46.779
Children just need love.

598
01:35:48.780 --> 01:35:52.019
Lots of love.

599
01:35:52.180 --> 01:35:54.979
And you have that.

600
01:36:03.580 --> 01:36:07.819
- I can't do it, Marie.
- Yes, you can.


601
01:36:09.300 --> 01:36:12.379
Lasse-mama.

602
01:36:21.580 --> 01:36:24.299
You can do it.

603
01:36:37.660 --> 01:36:39.499
Ht Astrid..

604
01:36:39.700 --> 01:36:44.699
I've thought an awful lot about what
you wrote in The Brothers Lionheart.


605
01:36:44.820 --> 01:36:49.259
That there are things
you just have to do.


606
01:36:49.420 --> 01:36:54.259
Sometimes I have to defend
my little brother against other boys.


607
01:36:54.420 --> 01:36:57.139
It's hard, but I have to..

608
01:36:58.260 --> 01:37:02.179
If I didn't, I wouldn't be a person,
but a little piece of dirt,


609
01:37:02.340 --> 01:37:04.899
and 1 don't want to be that..

610
01:37:31.380 --> 01:37:33.539
Come here.

611
01:37:44.860 --> 01:37:48.259
I've borrowed a nice bed for you.

612
01:37:48.420 --> 01:37:50.899
Lasse's very own bed.

613
01:37:55.100 --> 01:37:57.819
We have our own entrance.

614
01:38:01.420 --> 01:38:04.859
Tomorrow we can go to the park.

615
01:38:07.460 --> 01:38:11.299
And see if we can find
a good tree to climb.


616
01:38:21.820 --> 01:38:25.139
Lasse, are you hungry?

617
01:38:25.300 --> 01:38:28.059
I can't understand you.

618
01:38:30.980 --> 01:38:33.499
(In Danish)
Are you hungry?


619
01:38:35.580 --> 01:38:38.059
(In Danish)
Are you hungry, Lasse?


620
01:38:38.220 --> 01:38:40.939
I miss my mum.

621
01:38:49.100 --> 01:38:51.299
Come here...

622
01:39:04.780 --> 01:39:09.059
See that? Those are blackberries.

623
01:39:10.420 --> 01:39:14.059
You can eat them.
Have one.


624
01:39:19.060 --> 01:39:21.739
Oh, I'm so hungry!

625
01:39:25.780 --> 01:39:28.659
Here's some crisp bread...

626
01:39:36.740 --> 01:39:39.379
I want to go home to my mum.

627
01:39:59.180 --> 01:40:02.299
Look over there, Lasse! Swings!

628
01:40:12.380 --> 01:40:15.339
Why don't you go and try swinging?

629
01:40:21.980 --> 01:40:24.659
Isn't there anything you'd like to do?

630
01:40:31.700 --> 01:40:34.499
Do you want to go home?

631
01:40:41.580 --> 01:40:43.699
Lasse... eat something.

632
01:40:45.220 --> 01:40:48.739
I don't like it.

633
01:40:48.900 --> 01:40:51.139
You know what this is?

634
01:40:51.340 --> 01:40:55.739
It's crocodile pâté,
made from real crocodiles.


635
01:41:01.100 --> 01:41:03.939
Why don't we pretend that I'm Marie?

636
01:41:05.540 --> 01:41:11.179
(in Danish)
Lasse, eat your food like a big boy.


637
01:41:11.340 --> 01:41:15.699
And drink your milk.
Just like a big boy.


638
01:41:19.300 --> 01:41:22.059
You talk strange.

639
01:41:24.220 --> 01:41:28.459
That's because I'm Swedish.
And you're Swedish too.


640
01:41:28.700 --> 01:41:30.859
No!

641
01:41:31.060 --> 01:41:34.819
Lasse is Swedish,
and Astrid is Swedish.


642
01:41:36.460 --> 01:41:39.979
- And I'm your mother.
- No, you're not.


643
01:41:40.180 --> 01:41:43.299
Lasse, now eat your dinner
and then we'll play.


644
01:41:49.220 --> 01:41:52.659
Lasse, I'm your mother
and you'll do as I say!


645
01:42:13.500 --> 01:42:16.579
There there, Lasse.

646
01:42:27.420 --> 01:42:29.699
There, there...

647
01:42:31.140 --> 01:42:33.259
Come here...

648
01:43:09.460 --> 01:43:12.059
Am I interrupting?

649
01:43:17.140 --> 01:43:21.739
I was just about to write...
Sorry, Mr Lindgren...


650
01:43:21.900 --> 01:43:24.539
Come with me.

651
01:43:31.060 --> 01:43:35.099
There are a lot of spelling mistakes
in this morning's letter.


652
01:43:35.300 --> 01:43:39.939
The motoring holiday book
hasn't been sent. It's not like you.


653
01:43:43.660 --> 01:43:46.659
It's my son...

654
01:43:50.940 --> 01:43:54.059
He coughs and coughs.

655
01:43:55.100 --> 01:43:58.699
And I'm not getting any sleep
because I'm afraid he's going to die.


656
01:43:58.900 --> 01:44:02.099
I'll finish typing those letters.

657
01:44:05.100 --> 01:44:08.499
- I'm sending you home.
- You can't fire me!


658
01:44:08.700 --> 01:44:12.019
I'll fire you if you don't
go home to your son.


659
01:44:14.140 --> 01:44:18.299
- But I have so much work to do...
- That's an order.


660
01:44:18.500 --> 01:44:23.939
Go home and look after your sick boy
and don't come back until he's well.


661
01:44:49.780 --> 01:44:51.819
The doctor is here.

662
01:44:51.980 --> 01:44:56.059
Doctor?
I haven't called a doctor.


663
01:44:56.220 --> 01:45:00.219
Sture Lindgren sent me.
We're old acquaintances.


664
01:45:00.420 --> 01:45:03.699
- Sture...?
- There's no charge.


665
01:45:07.700 --> 01:45:11.459
Breathe in... and breathe out.

666
01:45:11.660 --> 01:45:13.539
Very good. Breathe in...

667
01:45:17.460 --> 01:45:19.659
Very good.

668
01:45:21.060 --> 01:45:24.659
And lean forward...
Lasse, can you cough for me?


669
01:45:28.180 --> 01:45:30.979
- Good.
- Will he be all right?


670
01:45:31.140 --> 01:45:33.619
It's whooping cough.

671
01:45:33.780 --> 01:45:38.179
There's not much to do
but let nature take its course.


672
01:45:39.820 --> 01:45:42.939
I'll be back in a week
to check on him.


673
01:45:59.420 --> 01:46:01.659
I can't sleep.

674
01:46:11.300 --> 01:46:14.699
I don't think I've ever told you...

675
01:46:16.100 --> 01:46:20.459
...about the town
where everybody drinks soda-


676
01:46:20.660 --> 01:46:22.899
- and says good morning all the time?

677
01:46:25.940 --> 01:46:31.379
It all started when the grown-ups
got angry with the children-


678
01:46:31.580 --> 01:46:35.899
- and sent them away in shame.

679
01:46:36.820 --> 01:46:42.059
And the children went to a new land
to live all on their own.


680
01:46:45.780 --> 01:46:50.059
The children
had to take care of themselves.


681
01:46:52.740 --> 01:46:56.219
But they were just children.

682
01:46:56.420 --> 01:46:58.939
They didn't really know what to do.

683
01:46:59.060 --> 01:47:03.299
So they slept
with their feet on the pillows-


684
01:47:03.500 --> 01:47:06.419
- and wore their clothes inside out-

685
01:47:06.620 --> 01:47:10.659
- and they said good morning
even when it was night time.


686
01:47:17.660 --> 01:47:20.179
Can I sleep in your bed?

687
01:47:25.500 --> 01:47:27.859
Of course, come.

688
01:47:48.220 --> 01:47:51.419
What happened next?

689
01:47:53.620 --> 01:47:56.699
Well, the children...

690
01:47:58.580 --> 01:48:01.419
...they did everything their own way.

691
01:48:03.700 --> 01:48:08.899
And they spent all their time
climbing trees and drinking soda.


692
01:48:10.060 --> 01:48:12.779
They were good at that!

693
01:48:50.260 --> 01:48:55.619
Hi, Astrid. My grandmother
looks after me and my sister.


694
01:48:55.780 --> 01:48:59.779
She says,
"Let the little children come to me. "


695
01:48:59.940 --> 01:49:04.419
She likes to play
even though she's old.


696
01:49:04.620 --> 01:49:07.459
I think you're like that too..

697
01:49:07.700 --> 01:49:12.059
All the children in your books!
I can tell you like us.


698
01:49:12.260 --> 01:49:15.979
You understand us.
You're on the children's side.


699
01:50:02.740 --> 01:50:04.899
You are a good person.

700
01:50:49.220 --> 01:50:51.259
There's my father!

701
01:51:00.340 --> 01:51:03.299
- Welcome.
- Thank you.


702
01:51:05.100 --> 01:51:07.779
- This is Lasse.
- Hello.


703
01:51:11.100 --> 01:51:13.779
I'm your grandfather.

704
01:52:13.940 --> 01:52:16.419
She's in the kitchen.

705
01:52:41.900 --> 01:52:44.739
Well... There you are.

706
01:52:48.100 --> 01:52:51.219
Say a proper hello to my mother.

707
01:52:52.420 --> 01:52:54.099
Hello, Lasse.

708
01:53:01.180 --> 01:53:02.499
Welcome.

709
01:53:30.660 --> 01:53:33.179
Tomorrow is Sunday.

710
01:53:34.660 --> 01:53:38.659
I wonder if you'd like
to go to church with us?


711
01:53:40.780 --> 01:53:43.339
If you'd like to.

712
01:53:51.620 --> 01:53:54.579
- Yes, we'll go.
- Thank you.


713
01:53:59.780 --> 01:54:02.499
Is there any coffee?

714
01:55:59.940 --> 01:56:02.099
Hi, Astrid Lindgren.

715
01:56:02.260 --> 01:56:06.859
We also wrote you a song.
It is your birthday!


716
01:56:06.980 --> 01:56:11.619
Our teacher helped us,
but we said what it should be about.


717
01:56:11.780 --> 01:56:15.779
Now we're going to sing it for you,
so you can hear it too.


718
01:56:15.940 --> 01:56:18.819
You write great books.

